Over 2,000 seniors make up our Class of 2024. They will follow a variety of paths that will unlock a myriad of opportunities in the coming years. Meet 8 seniors who reflected and shared what the last four years have meant and what lessons they’re carrying forward after graduation.

San José High seniors Noorpreet Thinda and Ian Parker are on track to graduate with a prestigious and globally recognized International Baccalaureate diploma. Read about their IB experience.

John Muir Middle School recognized for its commitment to building positive school culture and transforming its campus into a caring community.

Jelani Canser, the Director of Orchestra and Mariachi at Abraham Lincoln High and a long-time San José Unified employee is channeling his passion for music to inspire students to develop a love for music.
